---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageNav from '../components/PageNav.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="OpenClaw Setup Guide - Developer Productivity"
  description="Practical OpenClaw setup options across local machine, VPS, Railway, and DigitalOcean with security guardrails and deployment trade-offs."
>
  <main class="openclaw-page">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="wide-wrapper">
        <PageNav backUrl="/developer-productivity" backLabel="Back to Developer Productivity" />

        <header class="page-header">
          <h1>OpenClaw Setup Paths</h1>
          <p>
            If you are choosing where to run OpenClaw, use this page first. It covers local, VPS, Railway,
            and DigitalOcean with practical trade-offs and security controls.
          </p>
          <p class="companion-link">
            Need architecture and threat model context first?
            <a href="/blog/openclaw-self-hosted-ai-assistant-security-guide">
              Read the OpenClaw security deep dive
            </a>.
          </p>
        </header>

        <section class="summary-grid" aria-label="Setup summary">
          <article class="summary-card">
            <h2>Local Machine</h2>
            <p>Best for first setup and low-risk automation. Lowest blast radius if isolated well.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Fastest start</li>
              <li>No public exposure by default</li>
              <li>Great for debugging and learning</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
          <article class="summary-card">
            <h2>VPS (Generic)</h2>
            <p>Best for always-on runtime when you need stable background execution.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Persistent availability</li>
              <li>Full control of network and OS</li>
              <li>Requires active hardening</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
          <article class="summary-card">
            <h2>Railway</h2>
            <p>Good for quick managed deployment, but check runtime limits and secret handling carefully.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Fast deploy workflow</li>
              <li>Managed infra reduces ops load</li>
              <li>Platform constraints to evaluate</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
          <article class="summary-card">
            <h2>DigitalOcean</h2>
            <p>Good middle ground with solid control and predictable pricing on droplets.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Straightforward VPS model</li>
              <li>Easy firewall and VPC controls</li>
              <li>You still own patching and security</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
        </section>

        <section class="decision-section">
          <h2>Decision Matrix</h2>
          <div class="table-wrap">
            <table>
              <thead>
                <tr>
                  <th>Option</th>
                  <th>Time to Start</th>
                  <th>Ops Load</th>
                  <th>Security Control</th>
                  <th>Best Use</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr>
                  <td>Local</td>
                  <td>Very fast</td>
                  <td>Low</td>
                  <td>High (local only)</td>
                  <td>Learning, prototypes, safe workflows</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>VPS</td>
                  <td>Medium</td>
                  <td>Medium to high</td>
                  <td>Very high</td>
                  <td>Always-on personal or team runtime</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Railway</td>
                  <td>Fast</td>
                  <td>Low to medium</td>
                  <td>Medium</td>
                  <td>Quick managed deployment</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>DigitalOcean</td>
                  <td>Medium</td>
                  <td>Medium</td>
                  <td>High</td>
                  <td>Stable VPS with explicit control</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="guidance-section">
          <h2>Recommended Setup Sequence</h2>
          <ol>
            <li>Start local with loopback-only access.</li>
            <li>Add only low-risk tools and no third-party skills.</li>
            <li>Move to VPS after logging, backups, and token hygiene are in place.</li>
            <li>Use VPN or SSH tunnel for dashboard access.</li>
            <li>Expand capabilities only after policy checks and isolation are in place.</li>
          </ol>
        </section>

        <section class="security-section">
          <h2>Security Guardrails for Every Setup</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Never expose admin dashboard publicly.</li>
            <li>Use dedicated API keys with low permissions.</li>
            <li>Treat third-party skills as executable code and review before install.</li>
            <li>Separate OpenClaw runtime from sensitive file systems.</li>
            <li>Log every tool call and keep a simple incident rollback plan.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="playbook-section">
          <h2>Secure Local Install and Channel Connection Playbook</h2>
          <p>
            Use this sequence if you want to run OpenClaw on your own PC first, then connect Telegram or
            WhatsApp without opening an unsafe control plane.
          </p>

          <h3>Phase 1: Secure local baseline</h3>
          <ol>
            <li>Use a dedicated OS user and dedicated workspace folder for OpenClaw.</li>
            <li>Install from official OpenClaw docs only, then run dashboard-only for first validation.</li>
            <li>Keep the gateway bound to <code>127.0.0.1</code> and do not bind to <code>0.0.0.0</code>.</li>
            <li>Set a dashboard auth token and store it as an environment secret, not in Git.</li>
            <li>Enable only low-risk tools first (read-only files, no unrestricted shell).</li>
            <li>Only after local validation, add one chat connector at a time.</li>
          </ol>

          <h4>Install on local PC (official quick path)</h4>
          <p>
            Use one of the official install paths below, then validate the local dashboard before enabling
            channels.
          </p>
          <pre><code># Prereq
node --version   # Node 22+

# Option A (OpenClaw official installer, macOS/Linux)
curl -fsSL --proto '=https' --tlsv1.2 https://openclaw.ai/install.sh | bash

# Option B (npm global install)
npm install -g openclaw@latest

# Onboard + install daemon service
openclaw onboard --install-daemon

# Verify gateway and open dashboard
openclaw gateway status
openclaw dashboard</code></pre>
          <p class="note-text">
            If dashboard auth prompts appear, use your configured gateway token and keep access local-only.
          </p>

          <div class="config-note">
            <p><strong>Minimal secure env baseline (example):</strong></p>
            <pre><code>OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_HOST=127.0.0.1
OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_PORT=18789
OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_TOKEN=replace-with-long-random-secret</code></pre>
            <p class="note-text">
              Keep variable names aligned with your installed OpenClaw version and docs.
            </p>
          </div>

          <h3>Phase 2: Connect Telegram safely</h3>
          <ol>
            <li>Create a bot in BotFather and get the bot token.</li>
            <li>Add token in your local secret store or env file excluded from version control.</li>
            <li>Connect Telegram in OpenClaw dashboard or CLI channel setup.</li>
            <li>Restrict allowed chats or user IDs before enabling automation.</li>
            <li>Test text-only workflows first, then enable limited tool actions.</li>
          </ol>
          <pre><code># Telegram token example
export TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN="replace-with-your-botfather-token"
openclaw gateway status</code></pre>

          <h3>Phase 3: Connect WhatsApp safely</h3>
          <ol>
            <li>Use an official WhatsApp Business API path (Meta Cloud API or approved provider).</li>
            <li>Use a dedicated phone number for bot traffic, not your primary personal number.</li>
            <li>Store API token and webhook secret outside repo and rotate on schedule.</li>
            <li>If webhooks require internet reachability, expose only webhook endpoint, never dashboard UI.</li>
            <li>Start with read-only and notification tasks before any command-style automation.</li>
          </ol>
          <pre><code># WhatsApp QR login (OpenClaw web channel)
openclaw channels login
openclaw gateway --port 18789</code></pre>

          <div class="channel-grid">
            <article>
              <h4>Telegram default posture</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>Fastest channel onboarding</li>
                <li>Good for personal automation and alerts</li>
                <li>Use chat allowlist to reduce abuse surface</li>
              </ul>
            </article>
            <article>
              <h4>WhatsApp default posture</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>Better for business-facing workflows</li>
                <li>Webhook security and token hygiene are mandatory</li>
                <li>Use staged rollout before enabling privileged tools</li>
              </ul>
            </article>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="next-section">
          <h2>Next Read</h2>
          <p>
            For architecture, data flow, and threat model details, read:
            <a href="/blog/openclaw-self-hosted-ai-assistant-security-guide">
              OpenClaw for Builders: Architecture, Data Flow, and Security Guardrails
            </a>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="references-section">
          <h2>Further Reading and Deploy Links</h2>
          <p>
            For latest setup instructions and ecosystem updates, use these official and community links:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="https://openclaw.ai" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">OpenClaw official site</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://railway.com/deploy/openclaw" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">OpenClaw on Railway</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://marketplace.digitalocean.com/apps/openclaw" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">OpenClaw on DigitalOcean Marketplace</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://simpleclaw.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">SimpleClaw</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://github.com/HKUDS/nanobot" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">HKUDS NanoBot (GitHub)</a></li>
          </ul>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .openclaw-page {
    padding: var(--space-lg) 0 var(--space-xl);
  }

  .page-header {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .page-header h1 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
  }

  .page-header p {
    max-width: 800px;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }

  .companion-link {
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .companion-link a {
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .summary-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-md);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .summary-card {
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: var(--space-md);
    background: var(--color-surface);
  }

  .summary-card h2 {
    margin-top: 0;
    font-size: 1.15rem;
  }

  .summary-card p {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .summary-card ul {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .decision-section,
  .guidance-section,
  .security-section,
  .playbook-section,
  .next-section,
  .references-section {
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .decision-section h2,
  .guidance-section h2,
  .security-section h2,
  .playbook-section h2,
  .next-section h2,
  .references-section h2 {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .playbook-section p {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }

  .playbook-section h3 {
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
  }

  .config-note {
    margin: var(--space-md) 0;
    padding: var(--space-sm);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    background: var(--color-surface);
  }

  .config-note pre {
    margin: 0.5rem 0;
    overflow-x: auto;
    padding: 0.75rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    background: var(--color-code-bg);
  }

  .config-note code {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .note-text {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .channel-grid {
    margin-top: var(--space-sm);
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr));
  }

  .channel-grid article {
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: var(--space-sm);
    background: var(--color-surface);
  }

  .channel-grid h4 {
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }

  .channel-grid ul {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .table-wrap {
    overflow-x: auto;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 8px;
  }

  table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    min-width: 720px;
    background: var(--color-surface);
  }

  th,
  td {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    text-align: left;
    padding: 0.75rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  th {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-weight: 700;
    background: var(--color-code-bg);
  }

  .next-section a {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .references-section p {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }
</style>
